SOLUTION
(a) Since N is growing by 9% per year, we know that N is an exponential function of t with growth factor 1 + 0.09 = 1.09. Since N = 7.2 when t = 0, we have N = 7.2(1.09)^t.
(b) In the year 2011, we have t = 8 and N = 7.2(1.09)^{8} \approx 14.347 \hbox{ million passengers.}
(c) In the year 2000, we have t = -3 and N = 7.2(1.09)^{-3} \approx 5.56 \hbox{ million passengers.}
